## Batch Processing

### find_each

```ruby
# Process large datasets in batches (avoids memory issues)
Article.find_each(batch_size: 1000) do |article|
  article.update_stats
end

# Default batch_size is 1000
Article.find_each do |article|
  process(article)
end

# With conditions
Article.where(status: 'published').find_each do |article|
  send_notification(article)
end
```

### find_in_batches

```ruby
# Process in batches (get array of records)
Article.find_in_batches(batch_size: 500) do |articles|
  articles.each do |article|
    process(article)
  end
end

# Useful for bulk operations
Article.find_in_batches do |articles|
  Article.import(articles, on_duplicate_key_update: [:updated_at])
end
```

### in_batches

```ruby
# Update in batches (efficient for updates)
Article.where(status: 'draft').in_batches(of: 1000) do |batch|
  batch.update_all(status: 'archived')
end

# Delete in batches
Article.where('created_at < ?', 1.year.ago).in_batches do |batch|
  batch.delete_all
end
```

